  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 5 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This package is flagged at Model Risk Level 5 — the highest risk tier — because the pump design is novel, the clinical consequence of erroneous hemolysis predictions is severe, and the model is the sole basis for the tolerance decision. Several credibility factors remain not-assessed without documented justification, materially weakening the overall credibility claim.",
